<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3765] trappy ignoreCase behavior with StopFilter/ignoreCase</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3765</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Spinoff from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3751&quot; title=&quot;Align default Japanese configurations for Lucene and Solr&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3751&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
* If &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;stopWords&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; is an instance of {@link CharArraySet} (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;
* &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;makeStopSet()&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; was used to construct the set) it will be
* directly used and &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;ignoreCase&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; will be ignored since
* &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;CharArraySet&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; directly controls &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; sensitivity.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is really confusing and trappy... we need to change something here.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12541973">LUCENE-3765</key>
            <summary>trappy ignoreCase behavior with StopFilter/ignoreCase</summary>
