                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="13204520" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 13:51:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed patch: I think its the simplest solution, nuke the confusing ctors.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204534" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 14:02:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, for 4.0 i think we should go a step further and remove all this Set&amp;lt;?&amp;gt;/Set&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt; crap/instanceof/copying&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;instead stopfilter, etc should just take chararrayset, and this is what makestopset should return.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll update the patch. for 3.x we can just deprecate the two confusing nuked&apos; ctors from the first patch above...&lt;br/&gt;
so we can still make some improvement there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204535" author="steve_rowe" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 14:02:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204537" author="steve_rowe" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 14:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to removing Set&amp;lt;?/Object&amp;gt; in favor of chararrayset, too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204539" author="thetaphi" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 14:06:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to remove the Set&amp;lt;?&amp;gt; and hardcode method signatures to CAS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Changes on CAS should be separate (e.g. make it an interface, so we could have FSTCharArraySet and HashCharArraySet)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204620" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 16:21:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch for trunk.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found two traps/bugs and fixed them here as well (these will go in the backport too along with the StopFilter deprecations):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;DutchAnalyzer confusingly only used its default &apos;stem dictionary&apos; (e.g. kind/kinder, fiets) for the no-arg ctor, for other ctors, it would remain empty. This means stemming would be different if you passed an empty stopset.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Standard/ClassicAnalyzer had a ctor that takes File, i think we should deprecate this one, for the one that takes Reader.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="13204637" author="steve_rowe" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 16:50:04 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Standard/ClassicAnalyzer had a ctor that takes File, i think we should deprecate this one, for the one that takes Reader.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204639" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 16:50:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found a couple more Set&amp;lt;?&amp;gt; remaining (elisionfilter, solr factories). Ill update the patch to fix those too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204641" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 16:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
